name: Electronic Yin Yang
description:
Dark-light, negative-positive, zero-one, and any other pair that you can think of is a concept of dualism.

Is it accurate to assume that opposite forces in our world are complementary to each other? Has literature and language created this dualism or that it fundamentally exists in the laws of the universe?

Is polarity found in every conceivable property of the physical? (ie. hot-cold, stationary-mobile, soft-hard, sharp-dull, win-lose, ...)

Can you name any general construct that does not have an opposite? 

Pen on Paper Photographed
1498x1498 Pixels

2016
